    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-10T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-10T03:00:00-05:00" n="367"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d367">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/1870: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Standley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kuibyshev</hi> (<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >Moscow</hi>)</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1942-05-10T11:00:00+03:00">May 10, 1942—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>376. Department’s 203, May 6, 11 p.m. I had intended to discuss this subject last
                    evening with Vyshinski,<note n="74" xml:id="d367fn74">Andrey Yanuaryevich
                        Vyshinsky, Soviet Deputy People’s Commissar for Foreign Affairs.</note> but
                    in view of Tehran’s 145, May 8, 2 [<hi rend="italic">1</hi>] p.m., I did not do
                    so.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Standley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
